What exactly is cation exchange capacity and why does it matter so much for plant nutrition?

CEC refers to a soil's ability to hold positively charged ions (cations) like calcium, magnesium, potassium, and ammonium on the surface of soil particles. These cations are essential plant nutrients that would otherwise leach away with water movement.
